\f0\fs24 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Sir, here is the 
\f1\b full critical technical specification from A\'96Z
\f0\b0  for a production-grade 
\f1\b CHHAT Cigarette Brands / SKUs Detection System
\f0\b0 .\
My position is firm: 
\f1\b this should be built as a computer-vision-first retail-recognition platform with OCR, retrieval, structured fusion, and human review
\f0\b0 . That is more defensible than an LLM-first design for shelf images because retail-recognition research consistently points toward 
\f1\b detect \uc0\u8594  crop \u8594  match/retrieve
\f0\b0 , and newer fine-grained grocery work shows that 
\f1\b image + OCR text together
\f0\b0  outperform image-only recognition for subtle SKU differences. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.01733"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 arXiv}})\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 A. Aim and scope\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 The system\'92s primary job is to turn one or more retail shelf images into structured outlet-level outputs:\uc0\u8232 
\f2\fs26 \strokec2 mother brands present
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 , 
\f2\fs26 \strokec2 SKUs present
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 , 
\f2\fs26 \strokec2 estimated pack count by brand/SKU
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 , 
\f2\fs26 \strokec2 confidence
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 , 
\f2\fs26 \strokec2 review status
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 , and 
\f2\fs26 \strokec2 traceable evidence
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 . It should explicitly ignore non-pack artifacts such as shelf talkers, price labels, posters, and cigarette branding that is not a physical product pack. This mirrors the core challenge in shelf-product recognition, where real-store imagery differs sharply from reference imagery and packaging changes over time. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.01733"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 arXiv}})\
The system should have two official modes:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Brand-presence mode
\f0\b0 : best accuracy and lowest risk for operational reporting.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 SKU-resolution mode
\f0\b0 : more ambitious, more fragile, and therefore always confidence-scored with a stronger human-review safety net.\uc0\u8232 Do not contract around a single blended \'93accuracy\'94 number. Split quality by task.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 B. Business outputs and acceptance criteria\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 You should define acceptance around 
\f1\b five separate KPIs
\f0\b0 , not one:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Mother-brand presence F1
\f0\b0 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
