\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 W. Workload sizing and performance\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 Cloud Run GPU support is practical for inference services, but one key constraint is that you can attach only 
\f1\b one GPU per instance
\f0\b0 , and the GPU is attached to only one container. Google also documents startup around 
\f1\b ~5 seconds
\f0\b0  for Cloud Run instances with supported GPUs. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://docs.cloud.google.com/run/docs/configuring/services/gpu"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Google Cloud Documentation}})\
That means the clean architecture is:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls47\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 CPU service for API + orchestration\
\ls47\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 GPU service for detector / heavy visual inference\
\ls47\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 CPU service for OCR and fusion\
\ls47\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 optional separate VLM client service\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 Do not try to cram everything into one monolith with sidecars sharing the same GPU assumption.\
Sizing guidance:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls48\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 detector service scales horizontally by image\
\ls48\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 crop recognition scales horizontally by crop\
