\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 The core risks are not abstract AI risks. They are very specific:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls49\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 similar SKUs with tiny text differences\
\ls49\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 glare and reflections\
\ls49\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 partial pack visibility\
\ls49\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 poster/label false positives\
\ls49\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 packaging refreshes\
\ls49\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 skewed training distribution by region or surveyor\
\ls49\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 reviewers over-labeling unreadable crops\
\ls49\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 over-promising exact pack counts when stacked displays hide pack edges\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 These risks are consistent with the retail-recognition literature: subtle distinctions, multi-orientation packaging, and real-store conditions are the main reasons this problem is harder than generic object detection. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00138-024-01549-9"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Springer}})\
